This paper discusses a novel approach to artificial intelligence using projective simulation, which has applications in advanced robotics and quantum experiments. The paper focuses on the ability of the agent to generalize, which is an important feature of any intelligent agent. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses reinforcement learning problems, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application in advanced robotics suggests the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the agent's performance, which suggests the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the benefit of generalization, which is a key aspect of neural networks, suggesting the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
